ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend PSYC 627 to another student if they are really interested in the topic. If they are looking for a broad exploration of developmental psychology, a more general course might be a better choice.
I would recommend this course to any student interested in the nature and ontogeny of infants' social and cognitive abilities.
I would recommend, but I think the class is a good introduction to infant social cognition and related topics.

The class covers a wide range of infant cognition research and requires a decent amount of reading. I would recommend the class for anyone who wants to learn about the fundamentals of infant cognition research.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course was very relevant to my research and deepened my understanding of the discipline.
